      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GYM QUEEN (3) worked to find the lead and kept kicking only to find one better last time out over 1609m at this track, making it six minor placings in a row. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. That latest effort is good enough to win a race of this calibre. ASPEN BELLE (2) is a four-year-old mare from the Anthony Spiteri stable on debut. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Trial winner who looks above average. Any push in betting will add to the confidence. MISS KOMMUNICATION (1) is looming as a real threat after a better effort last start, finishing second at Kilmore over 1690m. WAITING FOR ANNA (4) cannot be left out after solid recent performances, the latest a sound fifth at Maryborough over 2190m.",
